# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We will use Prefix-Sum method here to find maximum element till every i'th index.
Then we will add out prefix_max at i'th position to our original vector at i'th position.
At last we will take sum upto every i'th index and push it into our answer vector.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:$$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:$$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<long long> findPrefixScore(vector<int>& nums) 
    {
        int n = nums.size();

        vector<long long> prefix_max;
        int max_current=nums[0];
        prefix_max.push_back(max_current);
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++)
        {
            max_current=max(max_current,nums[i]);
            prefix_max.push_back(max_current);
        }

        vector<long long> ans;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            nums[i]+=prefix_max[i];
        }

        long long sum=0;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            sum+=nums[i];
            ans.push_back(sum);
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```
