# Approach
The key to solving the problem is literally by writing the arrays on a paper and figuring out where to add what. The given formula is `conver[i] = arr[i] + max(arr[0..i]) `.

Now, with this we can understand that conversion array will contain sum of element at i and maximum element till i. Hence, we need to keep track of maximum element till i and check for it first when we iterate. 

Next, we do not want to return the conversion array!  We are asked to return array of sums from 0 to i of conversion array. Hence, we'll keep track of sum and store that in the array to return it.

In the given solution, conversion array is not stored as it will just take extra space. But for understanding purposes, you can get to conversion array first and then iterate another loop to get sum/ans array.
