The createCounter function initializes and returns a new Counter object with an initial value passed as a parameter.

The Counter class has the following methods:

increment(): Increases the current count by 1 and returns the updated count.
decrement(): Decreases the current count by 1 and returns the updated count.
reset(): Resets the current count to the initial value and returns the new count.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- The createCounter function takes an initial value as a parameter and returns a new instance of the Counter class, initializing it with the initial value.
- The Counter class maintains two properties: init, which stores the initial value passed to the constructor, and currentCount, which stores the current count.
- The increment method increases the currentCount by 1 and returns the updated count.
- The decrement method decreases the currentCount by 1 and returns the updated count.
- The reset method resets the currentCount to the init value and returns the new count.

