# Approach
Count number of components and for every component count the number of edges and nodes.
if edges == (node)*(node-1)/2 then we can say that the it is a complete component.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(E+N)
    where E=number of edges
          N=number of nodes


- Space complexity: O(N+E)

