# Approach
In complete connected components e = nodes*(nodes-1)/2;
e = no. of edges in the component
nodes = no. of nodes in the component

Using dfs we can find e and nodes in each components.

In the dfs function every edge will be counted twice.
So the final condition will be
e/2 == nodes*(nodes-1)/2
e == nodes*(nodes-1)

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(E + N)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ --> 

- Space complexity: $$O(N)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ --> 


