# Intuition
Connected components can be found using simple DFS/BFS.
We only need to count number of `complete connected` components.
`Complete connected` components are those where every node is connected to every other nodes.
So for given numner of nodes in a component (say `n`), numnber of edges would be = n * (n - 1) / 2

**How?**
(n : nodes) - connected with (n-1 : other nodes) -> total edes = n * (n-1)
Each edge have been counted twice since this is an undirected graph.
So effective total edges = n * (n-1) / 2

Eg of complete conected component with n = 4

```
1 --- 2
|  X  |
4 --- 3
```
Here each node is connected with every other nodes.

# Approach
* Follow the DFS traversal.
* For each of the connected component, check if that component is complete connected using above formulae 
* increment the counter if above is true

# Complexity
- Time complexity: `O(V+E)`

- Space complexity: For Adjacency list: `O(V+2*E)`

# Code
```java
class Solution {
    private void dfs(List<List<Integer>> adj, boolean[] visited, int u, Set<Integer> vertices) {
      visited[u] = true;
      vertices.add(u);

      for (int v: adj.get(u)) {
        if (!visited[v]) {
          dfs(adj, visited, v, vertices);
          }
      }
    }

    private boolean isSubGraphComplete(List<List<Integer>> adj, Set<Integer> vertices) {
      int n = vertices.size();
      int countEdges = 0;
      for (int v : vertices) {
        countEdges += adj.get(v).size();
      }

      int edges = countEdges/2;
      return (edges == n * (n-1) / 2);
    }

    public int countCompleteComponents(int n, int[][] edges) {
      // Create adj list
      List<List<Integer>> adj = new ArrayList<>();
      for (int i=0; i<n; ++i) {
        adj.add(new ArrayList<Integer>());
      }

      for (int[] edge: edges) {
        adj.get(edge[0]).add(edge[1]);
        adj.get(edge[1]).add(edge[0]);
      }

      // Count number of connected components using dfs/bfs (dfs in this case)
      boolean[] visited = new boolean[n];
      int count = 0;
      for (int i=0; i<n; ++i) {
        Set<Integer> verticesList = new HashSet<>();
        if (!visited[i]) {
          dfs(adj, visited, i, verticesList);

          // increase the component count only if this component is complete
          if (isSubGraphComplete(adj, verticesList)) {
            count++;
          }
        }
      }

      return count;
  }
}
```

