We know that a component is complete only if it contains (n-1)+f(n-1) number of edges where n= number of nodes.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. call the dfs and get nodes count and total edges count of each component.
2. if it satisfies the condition of the complete component, increse the count by 1

