# Intuition
A component of graph can be imagined as all the nodes in the sub graph having same representive.
For this subgrah to be fully connected, the number of edges in the sub graph should be n*(n-1)/2 where n is the number of nodes in the graph (All the edges are unique).

The representatives, number of edges and members in graph can be easily maintained in DSU.
# Approach
1.) For all edges, take union of vertices of an edge, as they would be in same subgraph
2.) Now vertices are represented by their representatives in the subgraph, number of edges of each sub graph can be counted.
3.) Take any vertice of an edge and add 1 to count of edges of the family.
4.) Now for each representative check if edges = (vertices * (vertices-1))/2, if it is, add 1 to ans.
5.) Return ans.

# Complexity
e is the number of edges and n is the number of nodes in the whole graph
- Time complexity:
    Union operation is $O(1)$ and it is done e number of times ,i.e,
    $O(e)$ , then adding edges is also $O(1)$ done e times, i.e. $O(e)$. Then the families function iterates over all nodes in graph and checks for valid number of edges, $O(n)$

    Total
    $O(e + e+n)$
    ==> $O(e+n)$
- Space complexity: 4 arrays of size n is maintained.
- $O(n)$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    class DSU{
        public:
        vector<int> P;
        vector<int> rank;
        vector<int> cnt_edge;
        vector<int> cnt_members;
        int n;

        DSU(int N){
            n = N;
            rank = vector<int>(n,0);
            cnt_edge = vector<int>(n,0);
            cnt_members = vector<int>(n,1);
            for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
                P.push_back(i);
            }
        }

        int Find(int x){
            if(P[x]!=x) return P[x] = Find(P[x]);
            return x;
        }

        void Union(int a, int b){
            int x = Find(a);
            int y = Find(b);
            if(x!=y){
                if(rank[x]>rank[y]){
                    P[y] = x;
                    cnt_members[x]+=cnt_members[y];
                }
                else if(rank[y]>rank[x]){
                    P[x] = y;
                    cnt_members[y]+=cnt_members[x];
                }
                else{
                    rank[y]++;
                    P[x] = y;
                    cnt_members[y]+=cnt_members[x];
                }
            }
        }
        void addEdges(int u){
            cnt_edge[Find(u)]++;
        }
        int Families(){
            int ans = 0;
            for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
                if(P[i]==i){
                    int e = cnt_edge[i];
                    int v = cnt_members[i];
                    if(e == v*(v-1)/2) ans++;
                }
            }
            return ans;
        }
    };
    int countCompleteComponents(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        DSU dsu(n);
        for(auto&edge:edges){
            int u = edge[0];
            int v = edge[1];
            dsu.Union(u,v);
        }
        for(auto&edge:edges){
            int u = edge[0];
            dsu.addEdges(u);
        }

        return dsu.Families();
    }
};
```

