**See we just need to find number of nodes in a component and we have to check if each node of that component is connected to every other node of that component. We can use DFS to mark all node of a particular component but how can we check if each node is connected to eveery other node of that component , it is simple we can store every node of a component in a vector lets say "cnt" and we can iterate the cnt vector and check the the size of every node in the adjacency list if it not equal to (cnt.size() - 1) then it won't add to answer.**


