# Intuition

For connected component (acc to Question) 
each pair of vertices should have edge **(which is somewhat\* to complete graph)**

Edge - Vertices Relationship for a Complete Graph : ```|E| = V*(V-1)/2```


Since matrix is given for undirected graph so each edge is encountered twice
```eg 1 ---- 2 is same as 2 --- 1``` 

So now, edge-vertice relationship : ```|E| = V*(V-1)```



# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
* use dfs to count number of component
* simply count the on edges and vertices in a connected component and use the above eqn to check whether the connected component is a complete graph or not.

