# Intuition
Very simple intuition. Complete component => All nodes should be connected to eachother in a component. So we have to, 
1. Identify the components
2. Check node in the component is connected to every other node

Simple!

# Approach
1. DFS starting from every node
2. Accumulate all nodes in a list. This is the "path"
3. Check if each entry in the path we just found is having connections to every other entry in the path

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n) to do DFS, O(n) INSIDE each DFS to check if path is fully connected 
=> OVERALL O(n^2) CORRECT ME IF I'M WRONG

- Space complexity:
    O(n) for the stack recursion, O(n) for storing the path, O(n) for the hashSet (optimization)
=> OVERALL O(n) since no nesting is occuring. After the entire DFS stack is popped out, we use the stored path to verify completeness.

Well commented, read the comments and you'll understand. Hope this helps.

# Code
```
public class Solution {
    public int CountCompleteComponents(int n, int[][] edges) {
        #region Adjacency List and seen initialization
        List<int>[] adjList = new List<int>[n]; bool[] seen = new bool[n];
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            adjList[i] = new List<int>();
        }
        foreach(int[] edge in edges){
            adjList[edge[0]].Add(edge[1]); adjList[edge[1]].Add(edge[0]);
        }
        #endregion

        //Start DFS on every element to find all connected components
        List<int> path = new(); //Store all elements in a path in path list
        int count = 0; //Keep track of connected components
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            if(!seen[i]){
                DFS(i);
                //Increment count based on if path fully is connected
                count += CheckIfCompleteComponent(); 
                path.Clear(); //Start exploring new path
            }
        }

        return count;

        //Very simple DFS function, nothing fancy
        void DFS(int curr){
            if(seen[curr]) return;

            seen[curr] = true; path.Add(curr);
            foreach(int entry in adjList[curr]){
                DFS(entry);
            }
        }

        //Function to check if path accumulated is complete or not
        int CheckIfCompleteComponent(){ //Only 2 (1 and 2) criteria
            HashSet<int> set = new(); //Quickly creating a hashset for easy lookup
            foreach(int entry in path){ set.Add(entry); }

            foreach(int pathEntry in path){
                //(1) Each member in path should contain connections to all other membes in path
                //First we check the count (-1 because it won't contain that starting point itself)
                if(adjList[pathEntry].Count != path.Count - 1){ 
                    return 0; 
                }
                else{ //(2) Checking if each element is contained in it. 
                    foreach(int adjListEntry in adjList[pathEntry]){
                        if(!set.Contains(adjListEntry)){ 
                            return 0; 
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
            return 1; //If not a valid path, return 0, else return 1
        }
    }
}
```

