# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
 Firstly, In order to find all the connected components we need to do a DFS. 
 After this, the next step is to confirm whether the given component that we traversed is connected or not. 
For this, we just run a simple for loop on every node present in the set and check if the degree of the curr node is equal to size of set(i.e all nodes present in the componet) minus 1 it means that the componet is connected
After this condition has been checked we can now increase our res variable.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool isConnected(vector<vector<int>> &AL, unordered_set<int> &s)
    {
        //comparing degree of each node present in set since every node in a connected component
        //has a degree that is equal to total no of nodes in the component - 1
        int ExpectedDegree = s.size()-1;
        for(auto i : s)
        {
            if(AL[i].size() != ExpectedDegree)
                return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
    void DFS(int i, vector<vector<int>>& al, unordered_set<int> &s)
    {
        if(s.insert(i).second)//the second parameter tells whether the insertion was succesful or not
            for(auto j : al[i])
                DFS(j, al, s);
    }
    int countCompleteComponents(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<vector<int>> AL(n);
        int res = 0;
        //creating adjacency list
        for(const auto i : edges)
        {
            AL[i[0]].push_back(i[1]);
            AL[i[1]].push_back(i[0]);
        }
        //stores all nodes processed in a single DFS iteration
        unordered_set<int> ms;
        for(int i =0; i<n; i++)
        {
            if(ms.count(i) == 0)
            {
                unordered_set<int> s;
                DFS(i, AL, s);
                if(isConnected(AL,s))
                    res++;
                ms.insert(s.begin(), s.end());
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

