# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Just a normal bfs or dfs traversal to count the subgraphs.
1.Convert the edges into adjacency list for bidirectinal graph.
2.Traverse in the graph for every node mark if it is visited.Once the graph is visited completely calculate the vertices and edges at the same time and store it .
3.Each time after calculating for a subgraph check if the edges are equal to vertice*(vertices-1)if yeas increment the count.
4.Similarly calculate for each graph and check if it is complete.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->TC:-O(n)

- Space complexity:
