# Intuition By prefix array
he code calculates the cost of flipping characters in the string and finds the minimum cost required to make all characters the same. It does this by considering the cost of flipping characters up to each position and then calculating the remaining cost from each position to the end of the string. The overall minimum cost is then determined and returned.

# Algo 

1. First, we initialize some variables and containers to store information.

2. We go through the string and calculate the partial sums. These represent the cost of flipping characters up to each position. For example, if we have "0011", the partial sums would be [0, 1, 1, 4], indicating the cost of flipping characters up to each position.
We initialize the minimum cost as a very large value.

3. Next, we go through the string in reverse order. We calculate the remaining cost by considering the difference between adjacent characters. If the characters are different, we add the remaining cost of flipping the characters from the current position to the end of the string.

4. We calculate the current cost by combining the partial sum up to the current position with the remaining cost.
We update the minimum cost if the current cost is lower than the current minimum cost.

5. Finally, we return the minimum cost as the result.
I hope this simplified explanation helps you understand the algorithm better. Let me know if you have any further questions!

# Code
```
typedef long long ll;

class Solution {
public:
    long long minimumCost(string s) {
        int length = s.size();  // Get the length of the input string
        vector<ll> partialSums(length);  // Store partial sums
        ll remainingSum = 0;  // Track the sum of remaining characters

        // Calculate partial sums for flipping characters up to each index
        for (int i = 1; i < length; i += 1) {
            if (s[i - 1] != s[i]) {
                partialSums[i] += (partialSums[i - 1] + i);
            } else {
                partialSums[i] = partialSums[i - 1];
            }
        }

        ll minCost = 1e14;  // Initialize minimum cost to a large value

        // Iterate through the string in reverse to calculate the minimum cost
        for (int i = length - 2; i >= 0; i -= 1) {
            if (s[i] != s[i + 1]) {
                remainingSum += (length - i - 1);
            }
            ll currentCost = partialSums[i] + remainingSum;
            minCost = min(minCost, currentCost);
        }

        // Return the minimum cost
        return min(minCost, remainingSum);
    }
};

```

