solutions.content:
Operation-1 : Flip bits towards left
Operation-2 : Flip bits towards right

Just observe that
For the left indexes like (0, 1..) if we do operation-2 it will be very costly
For the right indexes like (n - 3, n - 2, n - 1…) if we do operation-1 it will be very costly
For the **mid index (indexes)**, both **operation-1 and operation-2 will be of almost equal cost**


So it would be better to **make all chars equal to ‘mid’ character of string**
So targetCh = s[mid]
By which we can 
**Apply “Operation-1” on the left indexes** of mid (if character is not equal to target)
**Apply “Operation-2” on the right indexes** of mid (if character is not equal to target)


Do we really need to manually perform the operation by flipping all the bits (left/right)
If not then how do we know what is the correct character at some index after some operations are done on it
We can optimize it
We can keep a count of operations done on both left and right indexes

So if char in string is str = ch
op = (operations done on it)
**If (op is even) : we flipped ch even no. of times => so no change**
**If (op is odd) : we flipped ch odd no, of time => flip ch**

```
class Solution {
public:
    long long minimumCost(string s) 
    {
        int n = s.size();
        int mid = n / 2;
        long long ans = 0;
        char target = s[mid]; 
        //we will make all chars of string equal to target

        int i = mid - 1, j = mid + 1;
        int leftOp = 0, rightOp = 0;
        //===============================================================================
        while(i >= 0)
        {
            char ch = s[i];
            if (leftOp % 2 != 0) //if odd operations done, FLIP CHAR
                ch = (ch == '0')? '1' : '0';

            if (ch != target) 
            {
                leftOp++;
                ans += (i + 1);
            }
            i--;
        }
        //===============================================================================
        while(j < n)
        {
            char ch = s[j];
            if (rightOp % 2 != 0) //if odd operations done, FLIP CHAR
                ch = (ch == '0')? '1' : '0';

            if (ch != target)
            {
                rightOp++; 
                ans += (n - j);
            }
            j++;
        }
        //================================================================================
        return ans;
    }
};

```

