# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
For the $i^{th}$ state, we have the following options:
- If the $i^{th}$ character is the same as the previous characters:
    1. We can either keep the $s[i]$ same as the previous characters. 
    2. Or we can change $s[i]$, but then we also have to change the previous $i - 1$ characters.
- If the $i^{th}$ character is not the same as the previous characters:
    1. We can either change $s[i]$.
    2. Or we can change the previous $i - 1$ characters.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The $dp$ that we calculate using the above algorithm will only give us the optimal answer if we do only prefix operations. But the problems says we are allowed to do suffix operations as well. Hence we have to calculate a $dp2$ using the same algorithm, the only difference being we will calculate it from the end of the string.

After these $dp$ and $dp2$ arrays are ready, for each $i$, we take the minimum of $dp[i]$ $+$ $dp2[i + 1]$, since we are looking for the most optimal solution. Also, since the characters can be either all $0$ or all $1$, hence the $dp$ and $dp2$ will have $2$ substates at the $i^{th}$ state.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $O(n)$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ --> 

- Space complexity: $O(n)$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long minimumCost(string s) {
        int n = s.size();
        vector<vector<long long>> dp(n, vector<long long>(2, 1e9));
        vector<vector<long long>> dp2 = dp;
        if(s[0] == '0'){
            dp[0][0] = 0;
            dp[0][1] = 1;
        }else{
            dp[0][0] = 1;
            dp[0][1] = 0;
        }

        for(int i = 1; i < n; i++){
            if(s[i] == '0'){
                dp[i][0] = min({dp[i - 1][0], dp[i - 1][1] + i});
                dp[i][1] = min({dp[i - 1][1] + 2 * i + 1, dp[i - 1][0] + i + 1});
            }else{
                dp[i][0] = min({dp[i - 1][0] + 2 * i + 1, dp[i - 1][1] + i + 1});
                dp[i][1] = min({dp[i - 1][1], dp[i - 1][0] + i});
            }
        }

        reverse(s.begin(), s.end());
        if(s[0] == '0'){
            dp2[0][0] = 0;
            dp2[0][1] = 1;
        }else{
            dp2[0][0] = 1;
            dp2[0][1] = 0;
        }

        for(int i = 1; i < n; i++){
            if(s[i] == '0'){
                dp2[i][0] = min({dp2[i - 1][0], dp2[i - 1][1] + i});
                dp2[i][1] = min({dp2[i - 1][1] + 2 * i + 1, dp2[i - 1][0] + i + 1});
            }else{
                dp2[i][0] = min({dp2[i - 1][0] + 2 * i + 1, dp2[i - 1][1] + i + 1});
                dp2[i][1] = min({dp2[i - 1][1], dp2[i - 1][0] + i});
            }
        }
        reverse(dp2.begin(), dp2.end());
        long long ans = 1e12;
        for(int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++){
            ans = min({ans, dp[i][0] + dp2[i + 1][0], dp[i][1] + dp2[i + 1][1]});
        }

        return (ans == 1e12 ? 0 : ans);
    }
};
```

