then we need to check if  s[i] != s[i+1] then it compares i + 1, representing the distance from the start of the string to the current character, and n - i - 1, representing the distance from the current character from the end of the string. The minimum of these two values represents the minimum cost of the swap.
mincost variable is incremented for every swap.
