# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Overthinking 
because I could not think of a one liner solution
# Approach

<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1) I created a prefix array which contains the cost i would spend if i change my array from the left end to this element.
Ex: 01000(1)0110
If i am at the bracket element and i want to change it (using the left side) then it becomes 0 then in the left i would change another 1 to get all the same elements.
>Like if i consider that element and want to change it by using the left side then it would change (1 current ele)->(next 0 to the left) -> (next 1 to the left) -> (next 0 to the left) -> so on..
>After using the left operation for that element now i would do the same from the same parity element in the right.

2) The suffix has the same logic as the prefix but the change i will make would be in the right direction of the array.
Ex: 0100(1)1000100
If i am at the bracket element and i want to change it (using the right side) then i becomes 0 , then i would change the next 1 to the right , then next 0 to the right and so on...

>Inshort:Prefix contains the cost of alternate 0's and 1's (the last occurance) from the current element in the left direction
like 0100(1) cost would be (5th element)+(4th element)+(2nd element)+(1st element)
Suffix Contains the cost of alternate 0's and 1's (the first occurance) from the current element in the right direction.
like 10(1)1001 cost would be (3rd + 5th + 7th)
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long minimumCost(string s) {
        int n = s.size();
        int cnt = count(s.begin(),s.end(),'0');
        if(cnt == 0 || cnt == n)return 0;
        long long pre[2][n];
        long long suf[2][n];
        memset(pre,0,sizeof(pre));
        memset(suf,0,sizeof(suf));
        for(int i = 0;i<n;i++){
            if(s[i] == '0'){
                pre[1][i] = i == 0 ? 0:pre[1][i - 1];
                pre[0][i] = (i + 1) + pre[1][i];
            }
            else{
                pre[0][i] = i == 0 ? 0:pre[0][i - 1];
                pre[1][i] = (i + 1) + pre[0][i];
            }
        }

        for(int i = n - 1;i>=0;i--){
            if(s[i] == '0'){
                suf[1][i] = i == n - 1 ? 0:suf[1][i + 1];
                suf[0][i] = (n - i) + suf[1][i];
            }
            else{
                suf[0][i] = i == n - 1 ? 0:suf[0][i + 1];
                suf[1][i] = (n - i) + suf[0][i];
            }
        }
        long long ans = LLONG_MAX;
        for(int i = 0;i<n;i++){
            if(s[i] == '1'){
                long long left = pre[1][i] + (i == n - 1 ? 0:suf[1][i + 1]);
                long long right = suf[1][i] + (i == 0 ? 0:pre[1][i - 1]);
                ans = min({ans,left,right});
            }
            else{
                long long left = pre[0][i] + (i == n - 1 ? 0:suf[0][i + 1]);
                long long right = suf[0][i] + (i == 0 ? 0:pre[0][i - 1]);
                ans = min({ans,left,right});
            }
        }


        return ans;
    }
};
```

