# Intuition

Lets look at a restricted problem where we can do change only from one side. And lets also assume that we have an some array:

```
x, x, x, x, ... X, 
```

for which the answer is `n` (the values for `x` does not matter and they can be different or equal). Now lets add one more character to our array:

```
x, x, x, x, ... X, Y
```

if `Y == X` the answer will be the same as previous array was already changed to have all numbers equal. If they are not the same, you need to flip all the values before Y (doing only one flip as they all have equal values). And that flip will cost us `i`.

So we have the following dp:
`dp_lr[i] = dp_lr[i - 1] + (i if s[i - 1] != s[i] else 0)`

----------------

So we know how to get results moving from Left to Right. We can do the same doing from Right to Left.

And to get the resulting answer we can try every position and find the smallest values of `dp_lr[i] + dp_rl[i]`



# Complexity

- Time complexity: $O(n)$
- Space complexity: $O(n)$

# Code
```Rust []
impl Solution {
  pub fn minimum_cost(s: String) -> i64 {
    let n = s.len();
    let s = s.as_bytes();
    let mut dp = vec![0i64; n];

    for i in 1 .. n {
      dp[i] = dp[i - 1];
      if s[i] != s[i - 1] {
        dp[i] += i as i64;
      }
    }

    let (mut res, mut cnt) = (dp[n - 1] as i64, 0);
    for i in (0 .. n - 1).rev() {
      if s[i] != s[i + 1] {
        cnt += (n - i - 1) as i64;
      }
      res = res.min(dp[i] + cnt);
    }

    return res;
  }
}
```
