[🎨 The ART of Dynamic Programming:](https://leetcode.com/discuss/general-discussion/712010/The-ART-of-Dynamic-Programming-An-Intuitive-Approach%3A-from-Apprentice-to-Master) to avoid TLE, we can preprocess the input to reduce the asymptotic bounds of considering all optimal possibilities.  Similar to Kadane's algorithm, we can track the "best ending/beginning here" for each `k`<sup>th</sup> ending/beginning value from `0..1` inclusive at each `i`<sup>th</sup> prefix index and each `j`<sup>th</sup> suffix index of the input string `s` formulated from left-to-right and right-to-left as `L` and `R` correspondingly, then we perform a linear scan to consider the cost of each `i`<sup>th</sup> prefix/suffix index candidate as `L[i][k] + R[i][k]` ending/beginning in the value `k = 0..1` inclusive.

**👉 Prefix 🤔 Recurrence Relation Details:** For each `k`<sup>th</sup> ending value from `k = 0..1` inclusive, there are two possibilities to consider each each `i`<sup>th</sup> prefix:

* **🚫 Case 1:** if `s[i] == k`, then there is **no additional cost** since we do *not* need to flip this bit.  Thus, we set the `i`<sup>th</sup> cost to the previous `i - 1`<sup>th</sup> cost.
    * if `s[i] == k` then `L[i][k] = L[i - 1][k]`

* **✅ Case 2:** if `s[i] != k`, then the **additional cost** is `i + 1`, ie. the cost to flip the current `i`<sup>th</sup> bit to ending value `k` *plus* the cost of flipping the previous `i - 1`<sup>th</sup> prefix to the *opposite* value of `k`.
    * if `s[i] != k` then `L[i][k] = L[i - 1][k ^ 1]`

**👈 Suffix 🤔 Recurrence Relation Details:** For each `k`<sup>th</sup> beginning value from `k = 0..1` inclusive, there are two possibilities to consider each each `j`<sup>th</sup> suffix:

* **🚫 Case 1:** if `s[j] == k`, then there is **no additional cost** since we do *not* need to flip this bit.  Thus, we set the `j`<sup>th</sup> cost to the previous `j + 1`<sup>th</sup> cost.
    * if `s[j] == k` then `R[j][k] = R[j + 1][k]`

* **✅ Case 2:** if `s[j] != k`, then the **additional cost** is `N - j`, ie. the cost to flip the current `j`<sup>th</sup> bit to beginning value `k` *plus* the cost of flipping the previous `j + 1`<sup>th</sup> suffix to the *opposite* value of `k`.
    * if `s[j] != k` then `R[j][k] = R[j + 1][k ^ 1]`

---

*Kotlin*
```
class Solution {
    fun minimumCost(s: String): Long {
        var A = s.toCharArray().map{ if (it == '0') 0 else 1 }
        var N = s.length
        var L = Array(N){ LongArray(2) }
        var R = Array(N){ LongArray(2) }
        for (i in 0 until N) {
            var j = N - 1 - i
            for (k in 0..1) {
                L[i][k] = if (A[i] == k) { if (0 <= i - 1) L[i - 1][k] else 0 } else { i + 1 + if (0 <= i - 1) L[i - 1][k xor 1] else 0 }
                R[j][k] = if (A[j] == k) { if (j + 1 < N) R[j + 1][k] else 0 } else { N - j + if (j + 1 < N) R[j + 1][k xor 1] else 0 }
            }
        }
        return (0 until N).map{ i -> (0..1).map{ k -> L[i][k] + R[i][k] } }.flatten().min()!!
    }
}
```

