# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Since we flip bits, for a prefix only 2 types of strings are possible.
So there is a scope for re-usability of subproblem solution (screaming DP!) [although later i found out a simple greedy exists ;-;]

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Let inv be the inverse of input string
s = "010101" => inv = "101010"
```
dp[i][0] = dp[i - 1][0] if s[i] == 0
else
dp[i][0] = i + 1 + dp_inv[i - 1][0]
```
Because if we flip a character, then entire prefix is flipped and hence we can use solution from the inversed prefix.

Divide the strings into two half and for second half only perform suffix ops.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(n)$$

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(2 * n)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long minimumCost(string s) {
        int n = s.size();
        if (n == 1) return 0;
        string inv = "";
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            inv += (s[i] == '0' ? '1' : '0');
        }
        // cout << inv << "\n";
        vector<vector<long long>> cost(n , vector<long long>(2 , 0));
        vector<vector<long long>> cost_inv(n , vector<long long>(2 , 0));
        cost[0][0] = (s[0] != '0');
        cost[0][1] = (s[0] != '1');
        cost_inv[0][0] = (inv[0] != '0');
        cost_inv[0][1] = (inv[0] != '1');
        int half = (n - 1) / 2;
        // cout << half << "\n";
        for (int i = 1; i <= half; i++) {
            if (s[i] == '0') {
                cost[i][0] = cost[i - 1][0];
                cost[i][1] = (i + 1) + cost_inv[i - 1][1];
                cost_inv[i][0] = (i + 1) + cost[i - 1][0];
                cost_inv[i][1] = cost_inv[i - 1][1];
            } else {
                cost[i][0] = (i + 1) + cost_inv[i - 1][0];
                cost[i][1] = cost[i - 1][1];
                cost_inv[i][0] = cost_inv[i - 1][0];
                cost_inv[i][1] = (i + 1) + cost[i - 1][1];
            } 
        }
        cost[n - 1][0] = (s[n - 1] != '0');
        cost[n - 1][1] = (s[n - 1] != '1');
        cost_inv[n - 1][0] = (inv[n - 1] != '0');
        cost_inv[n - 1][1] = (inv[n - 1] != '1');
        for (int i = n - 2; i > half; i--) {
          if (s[i] == '0') {
                cost[i][0] = cost[i + 1][0];
                cost[i][1] = (n - i) + cost_inv[i + 1][1];
                cost_inv[i][0] = (n - i) + cost[i + 1][0];
                cost_inv[i][1] = cost_inv[i + 1][1];
            } else {
                cost[i][0] = (n - i) + cost_inv[i + 1][0];
                cost[i][1] = cost[i + 1][1];
                cost_inv[i][0] = cost_inv[i + 1][0];
                cost_inv[i][1] = (n - i) + cost[i + 1][1];
            }  
        }
        long long one = cost[half][1] + cost[half + 1][1];
        // cout << cost[half][1] << " " << cost[half + 1][1] << "\n";
        long long zero = cost[half][0] + cost[half + 1][0];
        return min(one , zero);
    }
};
