we need to minimize the cost so invert which half is small.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
start from 1st index in the string, is not equal to i-1 then check which half is small.

if left half is small just add the cost to res 

else right half is small we invert values in right and add cost to res

Note:- loop is move in right side so, we need to maintain the invert string so, if flip is true it flip the i and i-1 values so we make sure we pick correct value in the string.

Dont need to over complete the fliping process we have only 2 values either 1 or 0 so dont think run extra loop and place the invert values in string then proceed further (it cause TLE as well this is brute force approach)

