# Intuition
Sum up the min cost for every change in bit.

# Approach
For the first half of the string, for every change in bit, we do first operation
For the other half of the string, for every change in bit, we do second operation
And magic, the answer is found!!

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long minimumCost(string s) {
        int n=s.size();
        long long ans=0;
        for(int i=0;i<n/2;i++) {
            if(s[i]!=s[i+1]) {
                ans+=i+1;
            }
        }
        for(int i=n/2;i<n-1;i++) {
            if(s[i]!=s[i+1]) {
                ans+=n-i-1;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

