# Intuition

This code is not as elegant as the other one use Math.min(i, n-i), but it does explain things well.

First finding, the cost is the number of characters get flipped, from left or right.
Second oberservation, you will always choose rule 1 if index is less than mid point, choose rule 2 if index is greater than mid point.

Last, Key point, when there's a char different from the previous one. you have two choices
op1: invert all characters before i (not include i) or 
op2: invert all chars from i (inclusive) to the end


Here Math.min just help to solve the obersavation 2 in an elagant way, it also helps once the cost rule get changed in case.

