# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Divide the array into two halves:
1. For the first half the cost will be minimum if we take the first operation since all our values lie before our midpoint or at it if we include the midpoint(I have included the midpoint in this approach)
2. For the second half all our observations are on the right hand side of the midpoint so the second operation is the choice of inverting the bits 

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We have two choices on our hands :
1. Make all the array elements equal to '1'
2. Make all the array elements equal to '0'
Use a function to solve for both scenarios and the result is taking the min cost of the two possibilities

**The main function in question:**

Assuming input string :'010101' and the scenario where we want to make all the characters equal to '0' aka all the bits are 0
string:'0 1 0 1 0 1'
- Start at the midpoint (n-1)/2 aka index 2 in this case
- **Solving for the left half[0 1 0] with cost formula (i+1) for inverting indices (0,i):**
        **1)** Initialize  cost=0 
             **2)** Since we are solving to make all the bits to '0' traverse from the mid point 2 towards the left and check if the character is not equal to '0' aka find the nearest '1' when traversing from the midpoint towards the left.
             **3)** In this scenario the '1' is at index 1 we invert the characters from (0,1)[1 inclusive] which makes the result : **[1 0 0]** and the cost(for i=1)=**0+(1+1)=2**
             **4)** But here comes the catch since we are not modifying the string itself we can still perform the inversion by just inverting the condition we are searching on so instead of checking for '1' we search for '0' and our actual string is still:**[0 1 0]** we encounter the first '0' at index 0 and now the cost(for i=0)=**2+(0+1) =3**
             **5)** We have now reached the end of the left half

 We follow a similar approach for the right half traversing from the midpoint to the end and the cost formula is **(n-i)** with n being the size of the string
- **Solving for the right half[1 0 1] with cost formula (n-i) for inverting indices (i,n):**
           **1)**  Since we are solving to make all the bits to '0' traverse from the mid point 2 towards the right and check if the character is not equal to '0' aka find the first '1' when traversing from the midpoint towards the left.
             **2)** In this scenario the '1' is at index 3 we invert the characters from (3,5)[5 inclusive] which makes the result : **[0 1 1]** and the cost(for i=1)=**3+(6-3)=6**
             **3)** Inverting the condition we are searching on so instead of checking for  '1' we search for '0' and our actual string is still:**[1 0 1]** we encounter the  '0' at index 0 and now the cost(for i=0)=**6+(6-4) =8**
             **4)**  Inverting the condition we are searching on so instead of checking for  '0' we search for '1' and our actual string is still:**[1 0 1]** we encounter the  '1' at index 5 and now the cost(for i=0)=**8+(6-5) =9**
            **5)** We reach the end of the string 
**Repeat the above steps with the choice of making all the bits to '1'**
**Take the minimum of the two costs as the final result**
# Complexity
- Time complexity:  $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:  $$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->


# Code
```
class Solution {
    public long minimumCost(String s) {
        return Math.min(this.solve(s,'1'),this.solve(s,'0'));
    }
    public long solve(String s ,char c){
        //left half from mid to index 0(start index)
        int mid=(s.length()-1)/2;
        int i=mid;
        char ch=c;
        long cost=0;
        while(i>=0){
            if(s.charAt(i)!=ch){
                cost+=(i+1);
                ch=ch=='1'?'0':'1';
            }
            i--;
        }
        //Resetting the search to the original character
        ch=c;
        //right half from mid to index n-1(end index)
        i=mid+1;

        while(i<s.length()){
            if(s.charAt(i)!=ch){
                cost+=(s.length()-i);
                ch=ch=='1'?'0':'1';
            }
            i++;
        }
        return cost;
    }
}
```

