# Approach
Take 2 cases i.e. either make all characters 0 or all characters 1 and take minimum answer of the two. Now to turn a character which is '1' to '0' at index i, we need to flip all indices from 0 to i and then to make the previous characters (before index i) back to their original values we need to flip all characters from 0 to i-1 index hence the total cost would be (i+1)+i, hence we  need to take minimum of the two cases i.e. flip from left end or right end and the minimum will be added in the answer. We have maintained two answers one for the case when we are turning every character to 0 if it is not and the other case is for turning every character to 1.


