/*
    Let f(i,0/1,0/1) denote the minimum cost of setting all the first i elements to 0/1 and having an odd/even number of flips to the right

Decision 1: No flipping
    f(i,w,t) = f(i-1,w,t)                       w = t^si
Decision 2: Flip to the left only
    f(i,0,t) = f(i-1,1,t) + i                   t^si == 1
    f(i,1,t) = f(i-1,0,t) + i                   t^si == 0
Decision 3: Flip to the right only
    f(i,0,t^1) = f(i-1,0,t) + (n+1-i)           t^si == 1
    f(i,1,t^1) = f(i-1,1,t) + (n+1-i)           t^si == 0
Decision 4: Flip on each side
    f(i,1,t^1) = f(i-1,0,t) + (n+1)             t^si == 1
    f(i,0,t^1) = f(i-1,1,t) + (n+1)             t^si == 0

*/
