# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We are given a number n, we need to check whether every digit from 1 to 9 is present in the number which is formed connecting n + 2 * n + 3 * n.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
In the code we have made a string s, in which we have stored the number n, 2 * n and 3 * n in string format. We then have created a array of size 9 containing all elements equal to 1. We then ran a for loop till the length of string and checking the value of element at the index (s.charAt(i) - '0') - 1 if it is equal to 1 then changing it to zero and if already equal to 0 then returning false which means a number is repeated in the string. And also checking that (s.charAt(i) - '0') - 1 should be greater than 0 because if less than 0 will give a error as there is no index -1 or less in the array.

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public boolean isFascinating(int n) {

        String s = String.valueOf(n) + String.valueOf(2*n) + String.valueOf(3*n);

        int[] arr = new int[9];
        Arrays.fill(arr,1);

        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
            int j = s.charAt(i) - '0';
            if(j-1<0){
                return false;
            }
            if(arr[j-1] == 0){
                return false;
            }else{
                arr[j-1] = 0;
            }
        }

        for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++){
            if(arr[i]!=0){
                return false;
            }
        }

        return true;

    }
}
```

