# Approach
- Convert the input number n into a string str.
- Compute n2 = 2 * n and n3 = 3 * n.
- Concatenate str with the strings representing n2 and n3.
- Initialize an array digitCount of size 10 to keep track of the count of each digit from 0 to 9.
- Iterate through each character in string.
-If the character is '0', return false as fascinating numbers should not contain any zeros.
-Increment the count of the corresponding digit in digitCount.
-Check if each digit from 1 to 9 appears exactly once in digitCount. If not, return false.
-If all conditions are satisfied, return true as the number is fascinating.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool isFascinating(int n) {
    string str = to_string(n);
    int n2 = n * 2;
    int n3 = n * 3;
    str += to_string(n2);
    str += to_string(n3);

    vector<int> digitCount(10); // count of each digit from 0 to 9

    for (int i = 0; i < str.size(); i++) {
        if (str[i] == '0')
            return false; // If any digit is 0, return false
        digitCount[str[i] - '0']++;
    }

    for (int i = 1; i <= 9; i++) {
        if (digitCount[i] != 1)
            return false; // If any digit appears more than once or none, return false
    }

    return true; // All conditions satisfied, return true
}
};
```
