# Intuition
if `3 * n >= 1000`, then you will have more digits that we can check. Afterwards just calculate the resulting concatenated number `(n * 1000 + 2 * n) * 1000 + 3 * n;` and go digit by digit to add them to binary array of all digits.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $O(1)$
- Space complexity: $O(1)$

# Code
```
impl Solution {
  pub fn is_fascinating(mut n: i32) -> bool {
    if 3 * n >= 1000 {
      return false;
    }

    n = (n * 1000 + 2 * n) * 1000 + 3 * n;
    let mut arr = [false; 10];
    while n > 0 {
      arr[(n % 10) as usize] = true;
      n /= 10;
    }

    for i in 1 .. 10 {
      if !arr[i] {
        return false;
      }
    }
    return true;
  }
}
```

