The first transfer from the additional tank will occur when 5 litres have been consumed from the main tank. Subsequent transfer will happen with the previous transfer of 1 litre has been consumed and 4 litres from the main tank. 

So the number of (1L) transfers is

$$transfers = min(additonalTank, (mainTank - 1) / 4)$$

and the total available fuel is 

$$totalFuel = mainTank + min(additonalTank, (mainTank - 1) / 4)$$


