# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We want to get the maximum distance travelled . This is possible in case of maximum utilization of fuel. This can be done by help of additional tank.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We can use additional tank only when we use up 5L of fuel from main tank so we will use only chunks of 5L of fuel. For Ever 5L fuel we will use up 1 extra L of fuel from additional tank by transfering it to main tank. 
> **Trick** here is to use the additional tank to its fullest and that can be done by seeing if main tank has fuel in multiples of 5 we can use basic maths to calculate that but here we will see the iterative approach in which we are just simulating the stated process.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
We will run the process till our main tank fuel is exhausted . So Time complexity is O(N). 
- Space complexity:
